data.title: Basics4Babies — Healthy Mothers Healthy Babies Coalition of Palm Beach County, Inc.
data.meta_description: Emergency baby supplies provided by Healthy Mothers, Healthy Babies Coalition of Palm Beach County.
data.meta_site_name: Healthy Mothers Healthy Babies Coalition of Palm Beach County, Inc.
data.text:
Individuals may receive no more than one pack of diapers, one container of formula and one baby food pack per child per 30 days.

-Women who are pregnant may receive newborn diapers once during their 3rd trimester. Proof of pregnancy will be verbal and documented on intake form.

-Diapers are available for children ages 0-3.

-Formula is available for children ages 0-12 months.

-Food packs are available for children ages 4-12 months.

-Special needs children older than age 3 will be served with proper documentation on file (IEP, etc.).

Individuals must provide the following at the FIRST pantry visit to be added to our data system:

-Photo ID (Must be a resident of Palm Beach County)

-Caregiver name and employment status

-Child/children name, age and date of birth

-Proof of child: birth certificate, discharge paperwork from the hospital, passport, crib card, or other documentation verifying child’s date of birth; Social Security cards are NOT an acceptable form for proof of child

** The Mobile Pantry will be temporarily closed from July 29-August 16, 2024 **

The Basics4Babies Mobile Pantry operates on Mondays and Wednesdays, rotating between sites in West Palm Beach, Riviera Beach, Lake Park, Royal Palm and Jupiter - with the exception of the following holidays: New Year’s Day, Martin Luther King Day, President’s Day, Memorial Day, Juneteenth, Independence Day, Labor Day, and Christmas Day.
